# Safeguard AI – Cyber Harassment Detection App

Build a Streamlit web application that scrapes Instagram comments, classifies them by toxicity using Detoxify, and generates FIR PDFs for vulgar content.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup

#### [NEW] [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/MUKESH SINGH/Desktop/safespace/requirements.txt)
Dependencies: `streamlit`, `pandas`, `detoxify`, `instaloader`, `fpdf`, `torch`.

---

### Instagram Scraper

#### [NEW] [scraper.py](file:///c:/Users/MUKESH SINGH/Desktop/safespace/scraper.py)
- Accept an Instagram post URL (shortcode extraction via regex).
- Use `instaloader` to fetch the post and extract up to 20 comments.
- Return a list of `{"username": ..., "comment": ...}` dicts.
- Graceful error handling for private/invalid posts.

---

### Toxicity Analyzer

#### [NEW] [analyzer.py](file:///c:/Users/MUKESH SINGH/Desktop/safespace/analyzer.py)
- Load `Detoxify("original")` model.
- For each comment, compute a combined toxicity score (max of all Detoxify label scores).
- Classify severity: `Low` (<0.25), `Medium` (0.25–0.5), `High` (0.5–0.75), `Vulgar` (>0.75).
- Return a Pandas DataFrame with columns: `Username`, `Comment`, `Toxicity Score`, `Severity`.

---

### FIR PDF Generator

#### [NEW] [fir_generator.py](file:///c:/Users/MUKESH SINGH/Desktop/safespace/fir_generator.py)
- Generate a styled FIR PDF using `fpdf`.
- Include: timestamp, comment text, toxicity score, severity, and statutory warning citing cyber harassment laws (IT Act §66A, §67, IPC §509).
- Return PDF as bytes for Streamlit download.

---

### Streamlit Dashboard

#### [NEW] [app.py](file:///c:/Users/MUKESH SINGH/Desktop/safespace/app.py)
- Title bar: **Safeguard AI – Cyber Harassment Detection**.
- Sidebar with Instagram URL input + "Analyze Comments" button.
- Main area: styled DataFrame table with red-highlighted vulgar rows.
- Per-row "Download FIR" buttons for vulgar comments.
- Summary metrics (total comments, vulgar count, avg toxicity).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Instagram scraping requires a **public** post and may need login cookies. The app will fall back to demo data if scraping fails, so the UI can always be demonstrated.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. Run `pip install -r requirements.txt` to confirm all deps install.
2. Run `streamlit run app.py` and verify the server starts on `localhost:8501`.

### Manual / Browser Verification
- Open `http://localhost:8501` in the browser.
- Verify the dashboard title, input field, and analyze button render.
- Click "Analyze Comments" **without** providing a URL → confirm demo data loads and the table displays.
- Confirm vulgar rows are highlighted in red.
- Click a "Download FIR" button → confirm a PDF downloads with correct content.
